how can I have multiple where clauses in a query?
You can combine multiple WHERE clauses using AND or OR operators. Here are examples:

```sql
-- Using AND (both conditions must be true)
SELECT * FROM logs 
WHERE uri LIKE '%suj%' COLLATE NOCASE
AND client_user = 'john@example.com';

-- Using OR (either condition can be true)
SELECT * FROM logs 
WHERE uri LIKE '%suj%' COLLATE NOCASE
OR uri LIKE '%planning%' COLLATE NOCASE;

-- Mixing AND and OR (use parentheses to group conditions)
SELECT * FROM logs 
WHERE (uri LIKE '%suj%' COLLATE NOCASE OR uri LIKE '%planning%' COLLATE NOCASE)
AND date(dt) >= '2024-01-01'
AND client_user = 'john@example.com';
```

You can add as many conditions as you need. Just remember to use parentheses when mixing AND and OR to ensure the logic is evaluated in the order you want.
