possible to truncate the line if it's more than 70 chars?
Yes! In SQLite you can use the `substr` function to truncate strings. Here's how:

```sql
SELECT 
    dt,
    CASE 
        WHEN length(uri) > 70 
        THEN substr(uri, 1, 67) || '...'
        ELSE uri 
    END as uri,
    client_user,
    app,
    object_id
FROM logs 
WHERE uri LIKE '%suj%' COLLATE NOCASE
AND uri NOT LIKE '%calculations%' COLLATE NOCASE
ORDER BY dt DESC;
```

This will show the full URI if it's 70 characters or less, and if it's longer, it will show the first 67 characters followed by '...'.

You can adjust the numbers (70 and 67) to whatever length you prefer.

